title._content: Aerial View of the Town of New Ulm, Minnesota, Founded by a Land Society, Composed of German Immigrants...

description._content: Original Caption: Aerial View of the Town of New Ulm, Minnesota, Founded by a Land Society, Composed of German Immigrants. The Site, on the Minnesota and Cottonwood Rivers, Was Established in 1854. in 1857 the Town Was Officially Incorporated. A Flour Mill Was Once the Town's Major Industry. New Ulm Had a Population of 13,000 in 1974. It Remains a Farming Area with Some Manufacturing Firms. in Addition to People of German Descent, There Are Ethnic Populations of Norwegian Swedes and Welsh in the Area.
